item.title: Getting Started with Multiple Imputation in R
item.description: library(dplyr) library(mice) library(foreign) library(car) set.seed(145) Whenever we are dealing with a dataset, we almost always run into a problem that may decrease our confidence in the results that we are getting - missing data! Examples of missing data can be found in surveys - where respondents intentionally refrained from answering a question, didnâ€™t answer a question because it is not applicable to them, or simply forgot to give an answer.
